00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:57,820
 One really important principle I have learned

443
00:14:57,820 --> 00:14:59,820
 in managing this is

444
00:14:59,820 --> 00:15:01,820
 understanding that my sphere of interest

445
00:15:01,820 --> 00:15:03,820
 is not the same

446
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:05,820
 as my sphere of influence.

447
00:15:05,820 --> 00:15:07,820
 I am concerned

448
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:09,820
 about the world at large,

449
00:15:09,820 --> 00:15:11,820
 but I certainly cannot influence it.

450
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:13,820
 I cannot change it.

451
00:15:13,820 --> 00:15:15,820
 So, should I give up?

452
00:15:15,820 --> 00:15:17,820
 Or, should I shift my focus

453
00:15:17,820 --> 00:15:19,820
 to the things that I can influence?

454
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:21,820
 It's easy to be

455
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:23,820
 overwhelmed by the world, but remember this,

456
00:15:23,820 --> 00:15:25,820
 the bigger picture is

457
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:27,820
 God's domain.

458
00:15:27,820 --> 00:15:29,820
 By partnering with Him, you get

459
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:31,820
 to let go of all of that,

460
00:15:31,820 --> 00:15:33,820
 and focus specifically on what you

461
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:35,820
 can do, and how you do it.

462
00:15:35,820 --> 00:15:37,820
 Think of John

463
00:15:37,820 --> 00:15:39,820
 chapter 1, verse 5, where it

464
00:15:39,820 --> 00:15:41,820
 says, "The light shines

465
00:15:41,820 --> 00:15:43,820
 in the darkness, and the darkness

466
00:15:43,820 --> 00:15:45,820
 has not overcome it."

467
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:47,820
 Even if you are the only

468
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:49,820
 light in a sea of darkness, it already

469
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:51,820
 makes all the difference, because darkness

470
00:15:51,820 --> 00:15:53,820
 is defined by the absence of light.

471
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,820
 So,

472
00:15:55,820 --> 00:15:57,820
 if we accept the limits of our spheres of influence,

473
00:15:57,820 --> 00:15:59,820
 how do we become

474
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:01,820
 a restorative presence in our work?

475
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:03,820
 It includes three primary practices.

476
00:16:03,820 --> 00:16:05,820
 Firstly,

477
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:07,820
 being rooted in Christ.

478
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:09,820
 Before we go about the work of restoration

479
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:11,820
 in the world, we must be people

480
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:13,820
 of God, and allow

481
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:15,820
 God to renew our hearts.

482
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:17,820
 Secondly, being a

483
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:19,820
 cultivator of community.

484
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:21,820
 Now, this serves two functions. Firstly,

485
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:23,820
 to be a restorative leader, we need to

486
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:25,820
 be in a community of support

487
00:16:25,820 --> 00:16:27,820
 and encouragement, but we

488
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,820
 also need to be creators

489
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:31,820
 of community, providing the

490
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:33,820
 resourcing, the support, and the flourishing

491
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:35,820
 to all.

492
00:16:35,820 --> 00:16:37,820
 And lastly, being an advocate

493
00:16:37,820 --> 00:16:39,820
 of justice in systems and structures.

494
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:41,820
 We're called to be leaders

495
00:16:41,820 --> 00:16:43,820
 who don't just address

496
00:16:43,820 --> 00:16:45,820
 injustice that results from an individual

497
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:47,820
 action, but from collective,

498
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:49,820
 institutional, and systemic practices.

499
00:16:49,820 --> 00:16:51,820
 In other words,

500
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:53,820
 no matter what our main

501
00:16:53,820 --> 00:16:55,820
 professional purpose

502
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:57,820
 in life may be, and I include in this

503
00:16:57,820 --> 00:16:59,820
 frankly, being a

504
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:01,820
 stay-at-home parent, for example, or

505
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:03,820
 being a stay-at-home spouse, or

506
00:17:03,820 --> 00:17:05,820
 a student at school, or university,

507
00:17:05,820 --> 00:17:07,820
 so not just traditional

508
00:17:07,820 --> 00:17:09,820
 things that we would consider to be

509
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,820
 work, but what you spend the majority

510
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:13,820
 of your time with.

511
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:15,820
 In all of these circumstances, you can

512
00:17:15,820 --> 00:17:17,820
 be a restorative presence

513
00:17:17,820 --> 00:17:19,820
 by being rooted in Christ,

514
00:17:19,820 --> 00:17:21,820
 choosing to cultivate community,

515
00:17:21,820 --> 00:17:23,820
 and being an advocate for justice.

516
00:17:23,820 --> 00:17:27,820
 Put in even more plain terms,

517
00:17:27,820 --> 00:17:29,820
 furthering God's kingdom

518
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:31,820
 is not just about what you do

519
00:17:31,820 --> 00:17:33,820
 on a day-to-day basis,

520
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:35,820
 how you do it is equally

521
00:17:35,820 --> 00:17:37,820
 as important.

522
00:17:37,820 --> 00:17:39,820
 I want to dig a little

523
00:17:39,820 --> 00:17:41,820
 deeper into this relationship between

524
00:17:41,820 --> 00:17:43,820
 the what and the how,

525
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:45,820
 and more importantly, the importance of

526
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:47,820
 the how.

527
00:17:47,820 --> 00:17:49,820
 In the story of the choosing of the seven,

528
00:17:49,820 --> 00:17:51,820
 worrying about the

529
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,820
 food rations of the widows

530
00:17:53,820 --> 00:17:55,820
 was definitely not the primary

531
00:17:55,820 --> 00:17:57,820
 objective of the twelve.

